With unemployment skyrocketing as companies are forced to make staff redundant due to the economic impact of the coronavirus pandemic, thousands of people have lost jobs or been forced to abruptly change career. The number of people seeking temporary work has reached record levels, and recruiters report being overwhelmed by the number of job applications. We’d like to hear from people who have made dramatic changes to their working life as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. You can get in touch by filling in the form below, anonymously if you wish. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact for publication before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.